= Paragraphs

Paragraphs are the basic building blocks of text content.

== Basic Paragraphs

This is a paragraph. It contains regular text that flows naturally.

This is another paragraph, separated by a blank line.

== Paragraphs with Formatting

This paragraph contains *bold* text, _italic_ text, and `monospaced` text.

This paragraph has a https://example.com[link] in it.

== Paragraphs with Line Breaks

This is a paragraph with a line break. +
The plus sign creates a hard line break.

== Paragraphs with Special Characters

This paragraph contains special characters: -- (em dash), ... (ellipsis), and -> (arrow).

== Paragraphs with Lists

This paragraph comes before a list:

* List item one
* List item two

This paragraph comes after the list.

== Paragraphs with Code Blocks

This paragraph introduces a code block:

[source]
----
function example() {
  return "Hello";
}
----

This paragraph follows the code block.

== Paragraphs with Block Quotes

This paragraph introduces a quote:

[quote]
____
This is a block quote.
It can span multiple lines.
____

This paragraph follows the quote.

== Paragraphs with Attributes

[.highlight]
This paragraph has a CSS class applied to it.

[#special-paragraph]
This paragraph has an ID.

== Multiple Paragraphs

First paragraph.

Second paragraph.

Third paragraph.

Each separated by blank lines.


